						<summary>

						<p>Uttarāpatīśvara temple, central shrine, north wall to the left of the dvārapāla images in front.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīra-Bhūpatirāya-uḍaiyār, Śaka 1332, (expired) Khara, Āvaṇi 2.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record refers to the perpetual lamp donated by Karppaka-nāyakaṉ, the <hi rend="italic">vāvittar</hi> of Pālaiyūr alias [Ma]lai-kiḻāṉ-vaḷam in Ūṟṟukkāṭṭu-kkōṭṭam in Toṇḍaimaṇḍalam for Uttarāpati-nāyakar of Tiruchcheṅgāṭṭāṅkuḍi. The record is probably unfinished.</p>						

						</summary>
